<!doctype html>

<!doctype html>

<html>
<head>
    <title>Gym Buddy</title>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link href="css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="css/bootstrap-theme.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="css/index.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <!-- this iss a comment in HTML -->

    <!-- HTML5 Shim and Respond.js IE8 support of HTML5 elements and media queries -->
    <!-- WARNING: Respond.js doesn't work if you view the page via file:// -->
    <!--[if lt IE 9]>
    <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/libs/html5shiv/3.7.0/html5shiv.js"></script>
    <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/libs/respond.js/1.3.0/respond.min.js"></script>
    <![endif]-->
    {{> tracking_code_script}}
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <!-- h1 through h6 are headers. The higher the number, the smaller the header -->
        <!-- p means paragraph -->

        <img src="images/logo.png" alt="Main Logo Gym Buddy" class="logo">
        <br><br>

        <div class="loginBox">
        <br>
        <form role="form" action="/login" method="get">
            <div class="form-group">
                <label for="username">Username:</label>
                <span id="helpButton2" class="glyphicon glyphicon-question-sign pull-right" aria-hidden="true" type="button" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal"></span>
                <input type="username" class="form-control" id="username" name="username" placeholder="Enter username">
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label for="pwd">Password:</label>
                <input type="password" class="form-control" id="password" name="password" placeholder="Enter password">
            </div>
            <br>
            </div>
            <br>
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" id="loginButton">Login</button>
        </form>
        <br>
        <div class="container-fluid">
            <button id="registerButton" class="btn btn-primary btn-block">Register</button>
            <br>
            <button id="helpButton" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" type="button" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal">Help</button>
        </div>
    </div>

<!-- Modal -->
<div class="modal fade" id="myModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
                    <h3 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">Help</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <div>
                    <h6> Welcome to Gym Buddy! Your one stop destination for expanding your social network, but getting healthier at the same time. Our goal is to create a easy to use system that allows our users to find new workout partners and make new friends at the same time. All you have to do is create an account through our simple registration form and let us know a little bit more about yourself. After you've given us some initial data, you can create a profile for running or lifting weights. Based off of the data you enter here, we'll find you a workout partner that best matches your skill level and availability.</h6>

                    <h3>F.A.Q.</h3>

                    <h4>I forgot my password, what do I do? </h4>
                    <h6>Yes, we are currently implementing a forgot password feature that should make it's debut in the upcoming few weeks. </h6>

                    <h4>Can I change my workout profile preferences?</h4>
                    <h6>Yes, you can simply click on the row in the table of the workout you want to change and use the dialog box that's presented to change your preferences. Make sure you hit "Save Changes" though.</h6>

                    <h4>Can I delete a workout profile?</h4>
                    <h6>Yes, you can click on the row in the table of the workout you want to delete and then scroll to the bottom and click the delete button. You will be prompted if you really want to delete that profile.</h6>

                    <h4>How can I contact Gym Buddy for additional support? </h4>
                    <h6>If you need additional support email aryamansharda@yahoo.com </h6>

                    <h4>Will you be expanding to more types of workouts? </h4>
                    <h6>That's the plan!</h6>

                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery.js"></script>
    <script src="js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
    <script src="js/index.js"></script>

</body>
</html>
